==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prodrome
<hw>Pro"drome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ running
before; <?/ before + <?/ to run: cf. F. <ets>prodrome</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A forerunner; a precursor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A premonitory symptom; a symptom
or sensation experienced by a person which presages the onset of a
disease or abnormal physiological event; <as>as, the <ex>prodrome</ex>
of an epileptic seizure</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prodromous</ent>⟦br⟧
